radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is visualized and measures up to 10 mm in diameter with minimal surrounding fat stranding. No evidence of obstruction, wall edema, lymphadenopathy, free air or free fluid. The visualized portion of lung bases are clear. The liver shows no focal lesion or intrahepatic biliary dilatation. Clips in gallbladder fossa compatible with prior cholecystectomy. The spleen is normal in size and appearance. The pancreas and adrenal glands show no masses. The kidneys enhance with and excrete contrast symmetrically. The small and large intestine show no evidence of obstruction or wall edema. The bladder and rectum appear unremarkable. A small calcified fibroid is seen in the uterus. There are no aggressive-appearing lytic or sclerotic lesions.
